<subSubSection id="DDBD6569FFFA05628993FE8FE66115BA" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="951836E2FFFA05628993FE8FE66115BA" blockId="46.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis id="A7D3EAF0FFFA05628993FE8FE44E1510" bold="true" box="[199,335,332,357]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F1364B13FFFA0562880CFE8FE74A1511" author="Woodley, N. E." box="[344,587,332,357]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" refId="ref23047" refString="Woodley, N. E. (2001) A World Catalog of the Stratiomyidae (Insecta: Diptera). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 475 pp." type="book" year="2001">Woodley (2001: 338)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="52A74D61FFFA05628D58FE8EE09D1510" authority="Lindner, 1935" authorityName="Lindner" authorityYear="1935" box="[1036,1436,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Merosargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="A7D3EAF0FFFA05628D58FE8EE1F51511" box="[1036,1268,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">Merosargus apicalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F1364B13FFFA05628DA8FE8FE09D1510" author="Lindner, E." box="[1276,1436,332,357]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" pagination="396 - 413" refId="ref22113" refString="Lindner, E. (1935) Dritter Beitrag zur Kenntnis der sudamerikanischen Stratiomyiidenfauna (Dipt.). Revista de Entomologia, Rio de Janeiro, 5 (4), 396 - 413." type="journal article" year="1935">Lindner, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
identified by Lindner in the BMNH collection fit better in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="52A74D61FFFA05628ACBFEB3E6ED15F2" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[927,1004,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A7D3EAF0FFFA05628ACBFEB3E6ED15F2" box="[927,1004,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">Sargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but he did not transfer it to the genus because he had not seen the 
<typeStatus id="4A1C8840FFFA056288BBFE56E71E15D8" box="[495,543,405,429]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">type</typeStatus>
specimen. After studying photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="4A1C8840FFFA05628D6BFE56E16E15D8" box="[1087,1135,405,429]" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">type</typeStatus>
specimen, we agree with Woodley’s opinion and transfer the species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="52A74D61FFFA05628A59FE7BE65815BA" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[781,857,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Sargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A7D3EAF0FFFA05628A59FE7BE65815BA" box="[781,857,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="497">Sargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
